									<hr class="major" />
									
									<h2>Lessons Learned</h2>
									
									<h3>Strengths of AI in Design</h3>
									<ul>
										<li><strong>Rapid Visualization:</strong> AI can quickly explore design possibilities that would take hours to sketch</li>
										<li><strong>Communication:</strong> Photorealistic renderings help non-designers understand proposals</li>
										<li><strong>Inspiration:</strong> AI outputs can suggest unexpected solutions or combinations</li>
										<li><strong>Accessibility:</strong> Lower barrier to entry for design visualization</li>
									</ul>
									
									<h3>Limitations of AI in Design</h3>
									<ul>
										<li><strong>Lack of Context:</strong> AI doesn't understand community history, social dynamics, or political constraints</li>
										<li><strong>Physical Impossibilities:</strong> Generated images may show structurally unsound or impractical elements</li>
										<li><strong>Generic Solutions:</strong> Without specific prompting, AI tends toward generic "nice" spaces</li>
										<li><strong>Ethical Blindness:</strong> AI cannot evaluate social equity or gentrification impacts</li>
									</ul>
									
									<hr class="major" />
									
									<h2>Conclusion</h2>
									<p>AI proved to be a powerful tool for visualization and research acceleration in this urban design project. However, meaningful design still requires human expertise in problem definition, cultural sensitivity, ethical evaluation, and practical implementation. The most successful outcomes emerged from iterative collaboration—using AI to expand possibilities while applying human judgment to select, refine, and contextualize solutions.</p>
									
									<p>This project demonstrates that AI is best understood as a design assistant rather than a replacement for human designers. Future urban design education should emphasize AI literacy while reinforcing the irreplaceable value of site observation, community engagement, and ethical reasoning.</p>
									
